****************************************************************************************************************************************************************************************************************
Step 1: Log in to AWS
1.	Go to https://aws.amazon.com and click Sign In to Console.
2.	Enter your credentials and log in.
________________________________________
Step 2: Open S3 Service
1.	In the AWS Console search bar, type S3.
2.	Click on S3 under Storage.
________________________________________
Step 3: Create a New Bucket
1.	Click Create bucket.
2.	Bucket name: Type a unique name (e.g., department-website-2026).
⚠️ Must be globally unique across all AWS accounts.
3.	Region: Select the region closest to your users (e.g., Asia Pacific (Mumbai) if in India).
4.	Bucket settings for Block Public Access:
o	Click Edit.
o	Uncheck “Block all public access”.
o	Check the acknowledgment box.
5.	Leave the rest as default (Versioning, Tags, etc.).
6.	Click Create bucket.
________________________________________
Step 4: Enable Static Website Hosting
1.	Click on your new bucket name to open it.
2.	Go to the Properties tab.
3.	Scroll down to Static website hosting → click Edit.
4.	Select Enable.
5.	Choose Host a static website.
6.	Index document: type index.html.
7.	Error document (optional): type error.html (or leave blank if you don’t have one).
8.	Click Save changes.
9.	Note the Endpoint URL. It will look like:
Step 5: Upload Your HTML Files
1.	Go to the Objects tab in your bucket.
2.	Click Upload → Add files.
3.	Select your index.html (and other files if any, like CSS/JS).
4.	Click Upload.


Select image  and open

STEP 1: Go to Bucket → Permissions
1.	Open your bucket devshiv
2.	Click Permissions tab
STEP 2: Check “Block Public Access”
1.	Scroll to Block public access (bucket settings)
2.	Click Edit
3.	Make sure:
o	❌ Block all public access → UNCHECKED
4.	Tick the acknowledgement checkbox
5.	Click Save changes
⚠️ This only allows public access — it does NOT make it public yet.

***on browser ***
http://devshiv.s3-website.eu-north-1.amazonaws.com

